<content type="str">Charles William (Bill) Black, 69, of Fort Smith passed away Jan. 26, 2017. He was born Nov. 18, 1947, in Fort Smith. He was of the Christian faith, a member of the Flight Masters in Barling, a lifetime member of the NRA, a Marine Corp Veteran and a Purple Heart recipient. 
 
He is survived by his wife, Penny of the home; his stepmother, Julia Kerr of Iowa; four sisters, Debbie Daley of New York, Theresa Kerr and Julie Wells, both of Iowa and Debra Baty of Oklahoma; four brothers, Kenny Kerr of Iowa, Quincy Kerr and Stacy Kerr, both of Florida and Dave Carson of Fort Smith. 
 
Funeral service will be 12:30 p.m. Tuesday at Lewis-Roberts Funeral Chapel, 4817 Kelley Highway, Fort Smith with interment to follow with military honors at the U.S. National Cemetery in Fort Smith. 
 
Pallbearers will be Chris Hoyle, Bobby Coutu, Robert Waite, Robert Salisbury, John Duncan and Ronnie Burns. Honorary pallbearers will be The Age Spots, nieces and nephews, great-nieces and -nephews, Philip Baker, Felipe Aguilar and Scott Hoyle. 
 
Visitation will be held 5-7 p.m. Monday at Lewis-Roberts Funeral Chapel in Fort Smith. 
 
Memorials may be made to the Ronald McDonald House at Mercy Hospital, 7301 Rogers Ave., Fort Smith, AR 72903, or the Buddy Smith Home for Veterans in care of Next Step, 123 N. Sixth Street, Suite 200, Fort Smith, AR 72901. 
 
Arrangements under direction of Lewis-Roberts Funeral Chapel in Fort Smith.</content> 
